airman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff in his place.";i:8;s:59:"Once again he found himself serving with General Richard B.";i:9;s:80:"Myers USAF who became the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff on the same day.";i:10;s:181:"Just three weeks earlier on 11 September 2001 al-Qaeda operatives had launched multiple terrorist attacks against the United States striking the World Trade Center and the Pentagon.";i:11;s:81:"CHAIRMAN OF THE JOINT CHIEFS OF STAFF INSTRUCTION J-3 CJCSI 361001A DISTRIBUTION.";i:12;s:104:"A B C J S 1 June 2001 AIRCRAFT PIRACY HIJACKING AND DESTRUCTION OF DERELICT AIRBORNE OBJECTS References.";i:13;s:119:"This instruction provides guidance to the Deputy Director for Operations DDO National Military Command Center NMCC and.";i:14;s:184:"The Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff is the highest ranking military officer in the United States Armed Forces and the main military adviser to the President of the United States.";i:15;s:68:"Below is a list of all former Chairmen of the Joint Chiefs of Staff.";i:16;s:27:"General of the Army Omar N.";i:17;s:203:"B Oversight by Chairman of Joint Chiefs of Staff-1 The Secretary of Defense may assign to the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff responsibility for overseeing the activities of the combatant commands.";i:18;s:176:"Such assignment by the Secretary to the Chairman does not confer any command authority on the Chairman and does not alter the responsibility of the commanders of the combatant.";i:19;s:54:"Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff General David C.";i:20;s:206:"Jones presides over a meeting of the Joint Chiefs of Staff with the commanders of unified and specified command at The Pentagon the Joint Chiefs of Staff Gold Room also known as The Tank on January 15 1981.";i:21;s:70:"Extension of Term of Office of Vice Chairman of Joint Chiefs of Staff.";i:22;s:23:"100526 title I 107 Oct.";i:23;s:17:"24 1988 102 Stat.";i:24;s:158:"2625 authorized President to extend until June 1 1989 term of office of 